93.7	Scala_(programming_language)	Scala (programming language)	Scala ( -l…ô) is a multi-paradigm programming language designed to integrate features of object-oriented programming and functional programming. The name Scala is a portmanteau of "scalable" and "language", signifying that it is designed to grow with the demands of its users. James Strachan, the creator of Groovy, described Scala as a possible successor to Java.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/8/85/Scala_logo.png/200px-Scala_logo.png
